-- Mexico Stocks: Homex, Urbi, Geo, Industrias CH Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-09T22:53:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/mexico-stocks-homex-urbi-geo-industrias-ch-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. local time.  The IPC index fell 0.3 percent to 37,691.01.  Homebuilders rose for a third day as investors met with the
companies in New York amid optimism the government will support
the industry with subsidies aimed at curbing a housing deficit.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX*)  , Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, rose 2 percent to 39.87 pesos.  Urbi Desarrollos
Urbanos (URBI*)  SAB, Mexico’s third-largest homebuilder by
sales, gained 1.5 percent to 14.72 pesos. Corp. Geo SAB (GEOB
MM), Mexico’s second-largest homebuilder, jumped 4.3 percent to
20.15 pesos.  Industrias CH SAB (ICHB MM), Mexico’s largest steelmaker,
rose 1.7 percent to 55.72 pesos. Under current conditions,
 Industrias CH (ICHB)  may be added to the IPC in the next adjustment
planned for September, according to a running tally of stocks
that fit the criteria published yesterday by the exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
